Part II - Correlation among OriginalLoanAmount, ProsperRating and BorrowerAPR and the influence of BorrowerAPR, LenderYield on LoanStatus¶

by Maximilien Kpizingui¶

Investigation Overview¶

In this slide deck we are going to explore the correlation of the Original Loan Amount, ProsperRating on the BorrowerAPR. Besides, we will figure out how the BorrowerAPR and LenderYield may affect the loan status.

Dataset Overview¶

ProsperLoan dataset subjected to our analysis contains 113,937 observations and 81 features.Among these observations, we found that there were 1364086 missing values and some features which were not of interest in our analysis were also dropped. The wrangled data is further reduced with 76216 observations and 62 features. Finally among the wrangle data, we selected 17 features such as: [Term, LoanStatus, BorrowerAPR, LenderYield, ProsperRating (Alpha), ProsperScore, ListingCategory, Occupation, EmploymentStatus, EmploymentStatusDuration, IsBorrowerHomeowner, CurrentDelinquencies , IncomeRange, StatedMonthlyIncome, TotalProsperLoans, LoanOriginalAmount, LoanOriginationQuarter] to carry out our exploration

Visualization 3¶

Correlation between ProsperScore, BorrowerAPR and LoanOriginalAmount¶

The above scatter plot shows a negative correlation between ProsperScore and BorrowAPR. Moreover, the plot reveals that most of the loan original amount greater than 20k is taken by the pool of loan applicant having prosper score between 10 and 11

Correlation between EmploymentStatus and ProsperScore against BorrowerAPR¶

From the above scatter plot, we notice that

  • Employed people are diverse regarding the ProsperScore and BorrowerAPR
  • Full-Time and part-time tend to have higher ProsperScore and lower BorrowerAPR
  • Not-Employed & Self-Employed tend to have lower ProsperScore and higher BorrowerAPR
  • Retired people have higher ProsperScore and lower BorrowerAPR

EmploymentStatus vs BorrowerAPR in each LoanStatus¶

From the above plot, we notice loan status with Chargedoff & Defaulted tend to have a higher BorrowerAPR on average. The plot also reveal that the BorrowerAPR is least for those with the highest ProsperScore. Besides, BorrowerAPR is high for loan applicants with low ProsperScore. Moreover, borrowers with Part-time EmploymentStatus have the lowest MonthlyLoanPayment on average. Similarly those who have the lowest ProsperScore have the lowest MonthlyLoanPayment. We can also see that the defaulted and chargedoff loans have the lowest StatedMonthlyIncome on average.

Correlation among LoanOriginalAmount, BorroweAPR vs LoanStatus¶

The above plot shows that BorrowerAPR, LoanOriginalAmount are negatively correlated So the higher the loan amount gets the lower the interest rate becomes.

Correlation between LenderYield and Borrower APR against ProsperScore¶

The above plot shows that there is a strong positive correlation between lender yield and BorrowerAPR Furthermore, looking at the diagonal axis, it reveals that most of loan applicants with lower BorrowerAPR and LenderYield have higher ProsperScore. Conversely, loan applicants with higher BorrowerAPR and LenderYield tend to have lower ProsperScore
